on">                    How do you calculate "33% of firms per county"?                    <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>                </div>                <div class="faq-answer">                    <p><strong>Data Sources:</strong> State Bar rosters + Clio 2024 civil filings + Census Bureau business data</p>                    <p style="margin-top: 12px;"><strong>Calculation:</strong> 33% of solo/small firms (<21 attorneys, active license) actively handling inbound calls in high-volume civil practices:</p>                    <ul style="margin: 12px 0 12px 24px;">                        <li>Personal Injury</li>                        <li>Family Law</li>                        <li>Immigration</li>                        <li>Criminal Defense</li>                        <li>Employment Law</li>                        <li>Real Estate</li>                        <li>Bankruptcy</li>                        <li>Estate Planning</li>                        <li>Workers' Compensation</li>                    </ul>                    <p style="margin-top: 12px;"><strong>Example (Miami-Dade):</strong> 5,200 eligible firms  33% = 1,716 seats (total cap)</p>                    <p style="margin-top: 12px;"><strong>Minimum:</strong> 8 Founding Member seats (even in small counties)</p>                    <p style="margin-top: 12px;"><strong>Maximum:</strong> 120 seats (in largest metro counties like Los Angeles)</p>                </div>            </div>                        <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)">                <div class="faq-question">                    What if another firm gets TrueVow after I do?                    <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>                </div>                <div class="faq-answer">                    <p>That's expected! The cap is 33%, not 1 firm per county.</p>                    <p style="margin-top: 12px;">Even at full capacity (33% penetration), you maintain a <strong>+48% case volume advantage</strong> over the remaining 67% of firms without TrueVow.</p>                    <p style="margin-top: 12px;"><strong>Example in Miami-Dade:</strong></p>                    <ul style="margin: 12px 0 12px 24px;">                        <li>5,200 total solo/small firms</li>                        <li>1,716 firms can use TrueVow (33%)</li>                        <li>3,484 firms won't have TrueVow (67%)</li>                        <li>Your competitive edge is protected</li>                    </ul>                </div>
